My dearest Nimu/Gundu,

I don't know when exactly it happened, but somewhere between our conversations, laughs, silences, and those tiny moments that mean nothing to the world but everything to me, you became home. You have this beautiful way of existing calm yet intense, comforting yet exciting. With you, even ordinary moments feel special. A simple "hiiii" with that cute smile from you can change my entire mood, and your presence has this quiet magic that makes everything feel lighter, warmer, better.

I love how you make me smile without trying. I love how you understand me in ways I didn't even know I needed. I love your gym boy mode, your silliness, your seriousness, your cute smile and even the way you drive me a little crazy sometimes (okaaaaay, maybe more than a little üòÑ). But honestly, I wouldn't change a thing because all of it is you.

You make me feel safe and accept me to be myself unfiltered, imperfect and real. And that's rare. With you, love doesn't feel loud or rushed; it feels steady, comforting, and true. It feels like choosing each other again and again, even on the not-so-perfect days.

If I could give you one thing, it would be the ability to see yourself the way I see you kind, strong, beautiful, and so deeeeeeeply lovable. And if I could make one promise, it would be this: to care for you, to wish great things amazing things for you, to stand by you, and to keep choosing you‚Äîwith my heart, every single day.

Thank you for being you, Nimu. Thank you for finding your way into my life and staying. You mean more to me than these words can ever hold üí´
